text: Hurricane Edna was a powerful hurricane that hit the East Coast of the United States in September 1954. This storm made landfall over Cape Cod. New Hampshire and Maine were hit very hard. The storm caused 20 deaths. Edna hit a few days after Hurricane Carol had hit the same area. == References == Category:Category 3 Atlantic hurricanes Category:Hurricanes in New England Category:Retired tropical cyclone names Category:1954 in the United States Category:20th century in New Hampshire Category:20th century in Maine Category:1954 in North America Category:1950s in weather
